# ZMR 250 Carbon Fiber Frame – Specifications

## General
- Frame Type: X-Frame (ZMR 250)
- Material: 3K Carbon Fiber
- Wheelbase: 250 mm (motor-to-motor diagonal)
- Configuration: True X / H (variant dependent)

## Dimensions
- Wheelbase: 250 mm
- Arm Thickness: 4 mm
- Top Plate Thickness: 1.5 – 2 mm
- Bottom Plate Thickness: 1.5 – 2 mm
- Center Plate Thickness: 2 mm

## Weight
- Frame Weight: ~150 – 170 g (without electronics)

## Mounting
- Flight Controller Mounting: 30.5 × 30.5 mm (M3)
- ESC Mounting: 30.5 × 30.5 mm (4-in-1 ESC)
- Motor Mounting: 16 × 16 mm / 19 × 19 mm
- Stack Height Support: Up to ~25 mm

## Motor & Prop Compatibility
- Supported Motor Size: 22xx series
- Maximum Prop Size: 5-inch
- Recommended Props: 5-inch bi-blade / tri-blade

## Camera & FPV
- FPV Camera Size: Mini / Micro
- Camera Tilt: Adjustable (approx. 0°–45°)
- VTX Mounting: Rear plate / top plate

## Battery Mounting
- Battery Position: Top-mounted
- Battery Size Supported: 3S – 6S LiPo
- Mounting Method: Battery straps + anti-slip pad

## Use Case
- FPV Racing
- FPV Freestyle
- DIY / Beginner to Intermediate builds

## Notes
- Popular budget racing frame
- Easy availability of spare arms
- Strong and crash-resistant design
